The '''2014 Copa EuroAmericana''' was the second edition of [[Copa EuroAmericana]], a men's [[Association football|football]] [[Exhibition game|friendly tournament]] created by [[DirecTV]]. This edition took place in the [[Americas]] on 20 July – 2 August 2014.<ref>[http://comutricolor.com/confirmando-equipos-jugaran-copa-euroamericana-2014/ Se van confirmando los equipos que jugarán la Copa EuroAmericana 2014]</ref> Thirteen teams from [[CONMEBOL]], [[CONCACAF]] and [[UEFA]] participated in it.<ref>[http://www.copaeuroamericana.com/ Copa EuroAmericana] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130726005128/http://www.copaeuroamericana.com/ |date=2013-07-26 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.sportstats.com/soccer/world/copa-euroamericana/ Copa Euroamericana 2014 Stats]</ref> Europe, represented by [[Atlético Madrid]], [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]], [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]] and [[Valencia CF|Valencia]], won the cup by a 5–4 score, beating the Americas, represented by [[Alianza Lima]], [[Atlético Nacional]], [[Club América|América]], [[Estudiantes de la Plata|Estudiantes]], [[Junior F.C.|Junior]], [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], [[San Jose Earthquakes]], [[Club Deportivo Universidad Católica|Universidad Católica]] and [[Club Universitario de Deportes|Universitario]].

==Format==

Each match is played all 90 minutes. In case of a tie after the 90 minutes, the winner will be defined through penalty kicks. The confederation of the winner team of each match is awarded with a point, and the confederation with most points will be crowned champion.

